# Local dev only: web/public/data is a junction to the repo's data/ so the Vite
# dev server can serve dashboard.json, which CI otherwise copies into dist/ at
# build time. Git follows junctions like ordinary directories, so without this
# a `git add -A` would commit a duplicate, instantly-stale copy of the crawl.
# Note this ignores the data/ subdirectory only — web/public/fonts/ is real,
# and must stay tracked or the deployed site loses Styrene.
web/public/data/
